.SS "MEMORY COMMANDS"
These commands report/control memory usage.
.
.IP "\fBmemory/show\fR"
Displays some basic statistics about \fB\*(PN\fR's memory usage.
\fB\*(PN\fR also logs this information soon after startup and
periodically as its memory consumption grows.
.IP "\fBmemory/trim-on-growth\fR \fIon\fR|\fIoff\fR"
If this option is \fIon\fR, \fB\*(PN\fR will try to reclaim all unused
heap memory back to the system if significant memory consumption growth
detected.  \fIoff\fR by default.
